    <axiom component="lesson-plan">
        <title>Phase 4: Assessment (5 minutes)</title>
        <p xml:id="auto_q6dhxxxu">
            <alert>Q1:</alert> Copy the figure and draw the reflected image on the mirror line <m>M</m>.
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_ctmferz5">
            <alert>Q2:</alert> <m>\triangle PQR</m> has vertices <m>P(1,4),\, Q(3,1),\, R(5,3)</m>. Reflect in (a) <m>x</m>-axis, (b) <m>y</m>-axis, (c) <m>y = x</m>.
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_x3xuapzi">
            <alert>Q3:</alert> State three properties of reflection.
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_0qh7gr6r">
            <alert>Q4:</alert> <m>A'(6,-3)</m> is the image of <m>A</m> under reflection in the <m>x</m>-axis. Find <m>A</m>.
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_47oepzyd">
            <alert>Q5:</alert> A point is reflected in the line <m>x = 2</m>. The image is <m>B'(-1,5)</m>. Find <m>B</m>.
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_n6uzaxru">
            <alert>Answer Key:</alert>
            <ul>
                <li xml:id="auto_hiisy503"><alert>Q2(a):</alert> <m>P'(1,-4),\, Q'(3,-1),\, R'(5,-3)</m></li>
                <li xml:id="auto_4vpd4jyj"><alert>Q2(b):</alert> <m>P'(-1,4),\, Q'(-3,1),\, R'(-5,3)</m></li>
                <li xml:id="auto_41ad4yos"><alert>Q2(c):</alert> <m>P'(4,1),\, Q'(1,3),\, R'(3,5)</m></li>
                <li xml:id="auto_q8jnnf5j"><alert>Q3:</alert> (1) Image on opposite side; (2) equidistant from mirror line; (3) mirror line is perpendicular bisector of the segment joining a point to its image.</li>
                <li xml:id="auto_jozzmues"><alert>Q4:</alert> <m>A(6,3)</m></li>
                <li xml:id="auto_yvvdssix"><alert>Q5:</alert> <m>x = 2(2) - (-1) = 5</m>, so <m>B(5,5)</m></li>
            </ul>
        </p>
    </axiom>

    <axiom component="lesson-plan">
        <title>Differentiation and Extension</title>
        <dl>
            <li xml:id="auto_blu72v8r">
                <title>Struggling Learners</title>
                <p xml:id="auto_fxtjgu3r">
                    <ul>
                        <li xml:id="auto_q7so19j5">Provide grid paper with the mirror line already drawn.</li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_jo7i13py">Use a small mirror placed on the mirror line to visualise the reflection.</li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_pllc77n4">Start with vertical and horizontal mirror lines before diagonal ones.</li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_4lx57yzw">Give a step-by-step checklist: (1) draw perpendicular, (2) measure distance, (3) mark image, (4) connect.</li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_gefn2l0a">Use tracing paper to verify reflections by folding along the mirror line.</li>
                    </ul>
                </p>
            </li>
            <li xml:id="auto_dg0qn7pf">
                <title>On-Level Learners</title>
                <p xml:id="auto_7h758s5a">
                    Complete all problems including successive reflections, coordinate rules, and reverse (finding originals from images) problems.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li xml:id="auto_v1lcuam1">
                <title>Advanced Learners</title>
                <p xml:id="auto_38vldv4w">
                    <ul>
                        <li xml:id="auto_fqhu9u1t"><q>What single transformation is equivalent to reflecting in <m>y = x</m> then <m>y = 0</m>?</q> (Answer: <m>90°</m> clockwise rotation about the origin.)</li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_jqo4dig2">Investigate reflections in lines of the form <m>y = mx + c</m>.</li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_zgw8vohk">Prove that reflection preserves distances (i.e. the image is congruent to the object).</li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_dxkahm77">Explore patterns created by multiple mirror lines.</li>
                    </ul>
                </p>
            </li>
            <li xml:id="auto_7pqcnadc">
                <title>Extension Challenge 1: Successive Reflections</title>
                <p xml:id="auto_2jmiu7n7">
                    <m>\triangle DEF</m> has vertices <m>D(1,1),\, E(4,1),\, F(2,4)</m>.
                    (a) Reflect in the <m>y</m>-axis: <m>D'(-1,1),\, E'(-4,1),\, F'(-2,4)</m>.
                    (b) Reflect the image in the <m>x</m>-axis: <m>D''(-1,-1),\, E''(-4,-1),\, F''(-2,-4)</m>.
                    (c) What single transformation maps <m>\triangle DEF</m> to <m>\triangle D''E''F''</m>? (Answer: rotation of <m>180°</m> about the origin.)
                </p>
            </li>
            <li xml:id="auto_t43ekg3f">
                <title>Extension Challenge 2: Symmetry Design</title>
                <p xml:id="auto_ok0r0knp">
                    Draw a shape in Quadrant I, reflect it in the <m>y</m>-axis, then reflect both shapes in the <m>x</m>-axis. You get <m>4</m> copies of the shape, one in each quadrant — a symmetrical design.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li xml:id="auto_3gui0zvr">
                <title>Extension Challenge 3: Parallel Mirrors</title>
                <p xml:id="auto_1eftgkon">
                    If you reflect an object in two parallel mirror lines, the overall result is a translation. The translation distance equals twice the gap between the mirrors.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li xml:id="auto_q544ncf0">
                <title>Extension Challenge 4: Pool Problem</title>
                <p xml:id="auto_fyu9s3tk">
                    A swimmer is at <m>(3,2)</m>. Reflection in the <m>x</m>-axis gives <m>(3,-2)</m>. If a mirror is at <m>x = 20</m>, the image is <m>(37,2)</m> (using <m>x' = 2(20) - 3 = 37</m>).
                </p>
            </li>
        </dl>
    </axiom>

